                <Function>
                    <__p_name>register_block</__p_name>
                    <__p_description>Registers the wrapped class object as a block with the given name for the language currently being loaded. This must be called when a language is being loaded.</__p_description>
                    <__p_inlines>Define the wrapper descriptor function that actually takes the class object.

Register the given class object as a new block type. If this is the root block register it as such also.

Return the class object.

Return the wrapper function.</__p_inlines>
                    <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                    <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                    <Object>
                        <__p_name>name</__p_name>
                        <__p_description>The block's type name that is being registered. This must be unique among all block names of any one language.</__p_description>
                    </Object>
                    <Object>
                        <__p_name>root</__p_name>
                        <__p_description>Optional root Boolean that indicates the registered block is the root block of the language if set to true. Only one block type can be the root of a language.</__p_description>
                        <__p_assignment>False</__p_assignment>
                    </Object>
                </Function>
