                <__p_name>__main__</__p_name>
                <__p_description>Contains the main function where execution begins.</__p_description>
                <Function>
                    <__p_name>main</__p_name>
                    <__p_description>Begin execution of the program.</__p_description>
                    <__p_inlines>print the PID so the application can be killed. Qt likes to catch all exceptions without exiting.

Load the python language.

Create a new Qt application.

Create the parser thread, move the parser model to it, and then start its event loop.

Create and show an initial main window.

Start the GUI event loop, saving its exit code when it returns.

Request the parser thread quit and wait for it to stop.

Exit the application with the return code provided by the Qt application.</__p_inlines>
                    <__p_static>0</__p_static>
